import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='cx', y='cy')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx and cy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=name_counts.index, y=name_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between name and cx?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Name', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=True, color='blue', ax=ax, label='cx')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cy', kde=True, color='red', ax=ax, label='cy')
    plt.title('What is the range of values for cx and cy?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    ax.legend(['cx', 'cy'])
